\sqrt{75x} \cdot \sqrt{2x} \cdot \sqrt{14x} &= \sqrt{(75x) \cdot (2x) \cdot (14x)} \\
&= \sqrt{75 \cdot 2 \cdot 14 \cdot x^3} \\
&= \sqrt{2100x^3}
\end{align*}

Now, we need to simplify $\sqrt{2100x^3}$. We can factor 2100 into its prime factors: $2100 = 2^2 \cdot 3 \cdot 5^2 \cdot 7$. Therefore, we can rewrite the expression as:

\begin{align*}
\sqrt{2100x^3} &= \sqrt{2^2 \cdot 3 \cdot 5^2 \cdot 7 \cdot x^3} \\
&= \sqrt{2^2 \cdot 5^2 \cdot 7 \cdot 3 \cdot x^2 \cdot x} \\
&= \sqrt{(2 \cdot 5 \cdot x)^2 \cdot 21x} \\
&= 10x \sqrt{21x}
\end{align*}

So, the answer is $\boxed{10x\sqrt{21x}}$. </answer>

